```cpp
#include <hexi/hexi.h>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <cstdint>

struct NetworkPacket {
    uint32_t packet_id;
    std::string username;
    std::vector<uint32_t> scores;
    std::string metadata;

    void serialise(auto& stream) {
        // Serialize packet_id using direct serialization
        stream << packet_id;

        // Serialize username with prefix (length prefix)
        stream << username;

        // Serialize scores with prefix (count prefix followed by elements)
        stream << hexi::prefixed(scores);

        // Serialize metadata as null-terminated string
        stream << hexi::null_terminated(metadata);
    }
};

std::vector<uint8_t> serialize_packet(const NetworkPacket& packet) {
    // Create a buffer_adaptor with the empty vector as the underlying buffer
    std::vector<uint8_t> buffer;
    hexi::buffer_adaptor<std::vector<uint8_t>> adaptor(buffer);

    // Call packet.serialise(adaptor) to perform the serialization
    packet.serialise(adaptor);

    // Return the vector containing the serialized data
    return buffer;
}
```

## Explanation:

1. **Serialization Method (`serialise`)**:
   - `packet_id`: Uses direct serialization with `stream << packet_id`
   - `username`: Uses prefixed serialization (length prefix) with `stream << username`
   - `scores`: Uses prefixed serialization with `hexi::prefixed(scores)` which writes the count followed by elements
   - `metadata`: Uses null-terminated serialization with `hexi::null_terminated(metadata)`

2. **Serialization Function (`serialize_packet`)**:
   - Creates an empty `std::vector<uint8_t>` as the underlying buffer
   - Wraps the vector with `hexi::buffer_adaptor` to provide the serialization interface
   - Calls `packet.serialise(adaptor)` to perform the actual serialization
   - Returns the populated vector containing the serialized binary data

The implementation follows the Hexi library conventions as shown in the reference materials, using the appropriate adaptors for each data type as specified in the assessment objectives.

